\f0\fs24 \cf0 Erica\'92s family business\
\
Erica works in Sorocaba, a large city about 100 kilometres away from S\'e3o Paulo. Together with her husband and her two children she has regular routes and households that she visits with her old white bus. The rear side doors of the car have to be held together with lashing straps and rust breaks through the beige white paint in several places. On the rear window a hexagon is glued with tape, the left rear window is missing. A few meters beside the bus Erica's baby is lying in a buggy. The four-year-old sister sits next to it in a white and red patterned dress and is eating cookies. This is everyday life for the children. Early in the morning they set off to look for recyclable waste. On Tuesdays and Fridays they drive to housing estates, the rest of the days they are roaming the streets. \
\
